<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  Is everyone on our server going to have to start looking over their shoulder in case ADD might be comming? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
We already do.  In the last 3 weeks alone, we have had at least 3 run-ins with ADD, one time we even cought one of their members listening in on a raid channel that was not password protected, which ended up costing us a Severilious kill.<br>
<br>
From the quote posted from Graffe's by Blal Oceanos<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  The rule on Quellious now has gone from FFA but fair (ie if a guild is there, they got it first, even if they arent attacking it atm) to whoever pulls gets it.<br>
<br>
As you can imagine, this gets messy very quickly. Its tearing Quellious apart. And its sad. And im just as much to blame for it as everyone else, cus i want spawns too, so have to go about the same way as everyone else. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Considering the guild that Blal belongs to, and the recent occurences with them that my guild and others that have posted here have stated, I find this statement from him hypocritical to say the least.  <br>
<br>
I am not sure exactly what happened here, as I was not there, but I have always found Banelion to be an upstanding individual.  Every single time I have grouped with him, or have been a part of a raid with him, I have always left that group or raid feeling good about it.  I don't know if someone else was playing him during this fiasco, or if he has changed that much, or if the side of the story we are hearing from Tristadorn is askew, but in any case, ADD is building a fairly poor rep for themselves.  It is beginning to rival the rep that Vis used to have, when they were running roughshod over anyone and everyone.  <br>
<br>
I have several friends in ADD....Kaastle, Idias and other ex-guildies.  I hope that my views posted here do not affect our friendships, but if they do, cest la vie.<br>
